o the 1994 genocide in Rwanda to the bleak, prophetic landscapes of Cormac McCarthy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCatastrophical, The, in art. 0aCatastrophical, The, in literature. 0aCatastrophical, The, in motion pictures. 4aKatastrophe / i.d. Literatur. 4aKatastrophe. 4aKrise. 4aTrauma. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aArt.  aCatastrophes.  aCrises.  aFilm.  aLiterature.  aTrauma.1 aBJØRNSTEN, THOMAS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBRODESCO, ALBERTO, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCAPELOA GIL, ISABEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDIETRICH, RENÉ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aELIASSEN, KNUT OVE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGONÇALVES, DIANA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHANKOVSZKY, ANIKÓ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHOLM, ISAK WINKEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJOSHI, SARAH A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKALLENBACH, ULLA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKOOIJMAN, JAAP, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMACKINTOSH, ALEX, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMEINER, CARSTEN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeiner, Carsten, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNYIRUBUGARA, OLIVIER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNÜNNING, ANSGAR, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPERRET, CATHERINE, econtributor.4ctb4https:/